reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worked like a charm!
reviews.reviewText: Bought 2 to use in a desktop so I could recycle some RAM from a dead laptop. These worked great! I was hesitant given that we are adding a lot of trace wiring to the ram circuit. These worked just fine though. The SO DIMMs I used were 2133 DDR4. If it gets much faster, you'll probably run into issues, but these were exactly what I needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Does what it says it does with no fuss
reviews.reviewText: This product says exactly what the description says it does, I put a SODIMM in it that I had sitting around from when I upgraded the memory in my laptop and put it in one of my PC's and the computer detected the module without issue, highly recommended if you are looking for something like this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 20, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Definitely not aesthetically pleasing.
reviews.reviewText: These work perfectly as advertised. They took my Sodimms from my old laptop and I was able to perfectly transfer them into my desktop. I have been using these for about a week and there is no performance issues with using this adapter. The only reason I didn't give them a 5 star is because I definitely can't use 4 of these in my system, seeing as though the Sodimms get in the way of my cpu cooler. Definitely not low profile and they are not visually pleasing to look at. Good thing I don't have a glass side panel otherwise I would've spent the extra $40 and just got regular DIMMs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 13, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It work for now
reviews.reviewText: Ok so this works great after reseating the ram a few times. I’m using two 8gm sodims and it is fast enough for me not to notice. One note is that it would not recognize my two 32gm sodims which might be a limitation of the product. Definitely worth it your in between getting a much better upgrade but skip to something better if you can.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works so far!
reviews.reviewText: I watched a few videos about these, and they seemed to function most of the time, so I took a gamble. I only had one 8gb stick in my pc, and it was a weakness of my system. I was given an 8gb so-dimm card, so I thought I would give it a try.So far it’s working, running at 2133hz just like the description says. It was a bit of a tight fit in my ram slot. I had to reseat the so-dimm card and the adapter several times before my system recognized it. Once it did it has been going fine.I will update if anything goes sideways.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Works at DDR4-2133. But could better…
reviews.reviewText: First off it does work at 2133MT (DDR 2133) as specified. But it will not work at 3200.Not surprised.But it could work at DDR4-3200 if it had attenuators (resistors) on all the signal lines. The problem is at higher speeds too much of reflected signals to and from the ram begins to overlap with the proceeding data transfer. This is due to the introduction of another connector and stub lines that go between the motherboard DIMM socket and the SO-DIMM socket. Someone should make a converter with resistors on all the signal lines to fix this. The downside is you might have to run the DIMMs and IMC at higher voltage to compensate but it would work.The maximum frequency I was able to achieve was 1333MHz (DDR4-2666)
